Load assessments from a package/directory

Source: R/util-MakeAssessmentList.R
MakeAssessmentList.Rd

Load assessments from a package/directory

MakeAssessmentList(
  strNames = NULL,
  strPath = "workflow",
  strPackage = "gsm",
  bRecursive = FALSE
)

Arguments

strNames

array of character List of workflows to include. NULL (the default) includes all workflows in the specified locations.

strPath

character The location of assessment YAML files. If package is specified, function will look in /inst folder.

strPackage

character The name of the package with assessments.

bRecursive

logical Find files in nested folders? Default FALSE.

Value

list A list of assessments with workflow and parameter metadata.

Details

MakeAssessmentList() is a utility function that creates a workflow mapping for assessments used in Study_Assess().

Examples

MakeAssessmentList(strPath = "workflow", strPackage = "gsm")
